          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVI_mmyA1RySLMV__SgS8QxN4ipqcQzWBiGRRnN22gne7vs2OY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "UPDATE: I have pneumonia thanks to CityMD.\nORIGINAL POST:\n3 weeks ago I saw PA Steven Kapinos at the UES 86th Street (Btwn 1st&2nd St) location. I am a doctor and I\u2019m very well aware of my own health. I have a rheumatological condition for which I take an immunosuppressive medication, which compromises my immune system. It is rare for me to get sick.\n\nInfrequently (every 18 months or so) I\u2019ll experience early symptoms that need to be treated promptly, to avoid chasing a worse condition later with no immune system. This is exactly the situation I am in right now.\n\nI always make it a point to clearly communicate, but the PA who I saw treated the test instead of the person. He actually told me he was going to prescribe antibiotics, but never did, and never even mentioned it in his notes.\n\nNow, one month later, I\u2019m dealing with a more serious situation.\n\nHe was arrogant and dismissive, and like I mentioned, short sighted treated the test instead of the person.\n\nIn all fairness, this was the first bad experience I\u2019ve ever had at CityMD. Unfortunately, the unprofessional behavior, dangerous incompetence, and the degree to which that treatment has impacted my health, was so unwarranted that I would never risk my health with them again.\n\nAnd, good luck trying to contact CityMD to talk to anyone who cares. They purposely designed an impossible system to discourage anyone from trying to resolve this internally.\n\nTL;DR: I WILL NEVER USE ANOTHER CITYMD, and will be changing my Primary Care  doctor away from Summit Health, in order to completely avoid their system.\n\nI highly suggest you do too.\n\nTry Cornell or Mt. Sinai\u2019s virtual urgent care from their app. My Sinai also has a 24 hour Urgent Care Clinic at 310 E 14th street.\n\nIf you know a good, honest malpractice attorney I would appreciate it if you would make a recommendation of someone I could consider.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pSYVNWQjVVMEZXY2poNGFtSnVaWE5PYTNWSFJtYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xdf0e39ddde0873ab!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOjRaSVB5U0FWcjh4amJuZXNOa3VHRmc%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "Edited 3 weeks ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-06-03T06:01:05+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Judith Agisim",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "103744813805672406929",
          "user_review_count": 10,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIeye9tBCGl_yTi6l5GfNm8eVQPYLvD5AQSLaMih5iWUyCjxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "I had a wonderful, very positive experience this past Saturday evening at City MD on East 86th Street, NYC. I had been experiencing all day a light headed\nfeeling & afraid I would fall. I was fortunate to be examined by a brilliant PA, David Figueroa, who examined my neurological condition, and concluded I have BVVP vertigo. He explained what it is, reassured me it was manageable, gave me a prescription. He also had City MD secure an appointment with an ENT for me tomorrow.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xsVlQyeEtWUzAxZWtwVGRYQlVhbVpYV210b1FrRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xdf0e39ddde0873ab!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOllVT2xKVS01ekpTdXBUamZXWmtoQkE%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "2 weeks ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-06-09T00:01:38+00:00"
