        {
          "username": "evyiatar avraham omer",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "118418081732887962513",
          "user_review_count": 14,
          "user_photo_count": 2,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWdTgFYF4RFvZjFP1Du1NfPCtjbL5FvSgS4fOGyD0TWViwBdPfi=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "I visited a CityMD location on 86th Street at approximately 9:45 PM. The clinic\u2019s posted closing time is 11:00 PM. After completing all intake forms and being assessed by the nurse, I was told that I was dehydrated and that the provider would administer IV hydration.\nHowever, when the doctor, Tatyana Polovenko Kallman, MD, entered the room, the first thing she said\u2014before asking any questions about my condition or symptoms\u2014was that she would not provide hydration. Her tone was dismissive and unprofessional. When I asked for an explanation, she stated that the clinic was closing at 11:00 PM and that IV hydration would take more than an hour. She then suggested that I go to the emergency room instead.\nI questioned why I had been accepted as a patient, assessed, and charged if the provider had already decided not to treat me. I was told I would be refunded, and the receptionist (Ashlyn) processed the refund.\nI then requested the doctor\u2019s name and license number. The provider refused to provide her license number. I also asked for documentation stating that treatment was refused. I was told that I would be charged $50 for a note from the provider. Additionally, when I asked to speak directly with the provider, I was told I would need to be charged again to do so.\nThis experience was unacceptable. I was evaluated by staff and led to believe I would receive treatment, only to be refused care without any meaningful medical assessment, apparently due to the provider wanting to leave before closing time. The lack of professionalism, transparency, and basic patient respect from both the provider and front desk staff is very concerning.\nI will be escalating this matter to CityMD headquarters, as well as to the New York State Department of Health, and will be sharing this experience in a public review so others are aware.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2taTGRITndPRFIyYjFWcVpWRllSRzFtY1ZWMk5IYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xdf0e39ddde0873ab!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOkZLdHNwODR2b1VqZVFYRG1mcVV2NHc%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "a month ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-05-05T03:12:29+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Fatima Niangado",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "114771604929813093646",
          "user_review_count": 17,
          "user_photo_count": 1,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLdeMgILabh1cYjrWiGCCixliBPtIC6d_UiSqnDeu54eoDzakE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "I visited the CityMD on 86th Street today for a medical clearance and had an excellent experience thanks to Tay and Tyler.\n\nTyler checked me in and was extremely thorough. He asked the right questions and made sure I was being seen for exactly what I needed. I had previously gone to two other CityMD locations where my paperwork was not completed properly, but Tyler took the time to ensure everything was correct and complete before I was seen. I truly appreciated his diligence and professionalism.\n\nTay drew my blood and was superb. She carefully located the vein and only performed the stick once she was confident \u2014 which I really noticed because I\u2019ve had previous visits elsewhere where even physicians struggled. Her technique was gentle, confident, and painless.\n\nTogether they were a dream team. I was in and out of the clinic efficiently while still feeling cared for and taken seriously. This was by far my best urgent care experience. Thank you both for your professionalism and kindness!",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25odGRYWlpVWEZhWWw5R1JGVXdXRWt6YW1kaVdXYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xdf0e39ddde0873ab!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOnhtdXZZUXFaYl9GRFUwWEkzamdiWWc%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "3 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-03-01T01:21:18+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Perla Serrano",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "108197473926956391318",
          "user_review_count": 19,
          "user_photo_count": 2,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIlXhx7BQ2HtM06nfNIjxy-bbc1mFvtNcLemKj4D9RISCy7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "I visited this urgent care with my son on 05/07/26 after he suffered a minor cut that needed to be glued closed. The doctor was excellent with him, especially because he was extremely scared during the procedure. Unfortunately, the experience with the woman at the front desk staff and manager was completely different.\n\nI accidentally left my iPhone charger in the examination room and realized it less than 5 minutes after leaving. I immediately returned and politely explained exactly where I had left it. The woman at the front desk responded with a very annoyed attitude when I asked if she could quickly check the room. She came back almost immediately and said there was nothing there.\n\nI then asked to speak with the manager. The manager also seemed annoyed from the beginning and simply sent the same employee back to \u201ccheck\u201d again. Once again, they claimed nothing was there.\n\nAt that point, I respectfully asked if they could take me to the room so I could briefly look in the examination room myself since my son had just been treated there minutes earlier. I was told that it would be a HIPAA violation, which honestly made no sense considering we had just occupied the room and they themselves stated the room had not even been cleaned yet. Returning to the same examination room for a moment to look for a forgotten phone charger is not a HIPAA violation.\n\nI then asked if they could at least review the cameras or make a genuine effort to help locate it, and they laughed and said no.\n\nThe issue is not really the charger itself, but the way the situation was handled. The lack of professionalism, empathy, and basic customer service from the administrative staff is extremely disappointing. Their behavior honestly gives the impression that forgotten items are not taken seriously and possibly just kept instead of making an effort to return them to patients.\n\nI truly appreciated the doctor\u2019s care, but management and front desk staff seriously need better training in customer service and patient relations.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2s5Rk1sTTNjM0ZhTlVkSFMxQkNZbk15T1hoRWRsRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xdf0e39ddde0873ab!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOk9FMlM3c3FaNUdHS1BCYnMyOXhEdlE%7C%7C?hl=en",
